Citation.sAbstract: Binodal curves of 1-ethyl-3-methylimidazolium tetrafluoroborate ([Emim]BF4) + sodium  carbonate and 1-propyl-3-methylimidazolium tetrafluoroborate ([Pmim]BF4) + sodium carbonate  systems have been determined experimentally at T = (288.15, 298.15, and 308.15) K, respectively. An  empirical nonlinear expression which has four fitting parameters was used to reproduce experimental  binodal data. The tie-line data were successfully correlated by the Othmer-Tobias and Bancroft and  two-parameter equations. Good agreement was obtained with the experimental tie-line data with both  models. Factors affecting the binodal curves such as temperature and nature of ionic liquids were also  studied. It was demonstrated that two-phase area was expanded with a decrease in temperature, while  the absolute value of slope of the ties slightly decreases with an increase in temperature. However, the  binodal curves became more close to the origin with an increase in alkyl chain length of the ionic  liquids (ILs) on the investigated systems.
Citation.sTitle: Liquid-liquid equilibrium composed of imidazolium tetrafluoroborate ionic liquids + sodium  carbonate aqueous two-phase systems and correlation at (288.15, 298.15, and 308.15) K
